}} 'Fuy River' () is a river in the commune of Panguipulli, southern Chile. It
drains Pirihueico Lake and flows southward along the village of Neltume where it
joins Neltume River and creates together Panguipulli Lake. The river's origin is
near the village of Puerto Fuy.
